---

## Prerequisites

Before running the application, ensure the following are installed:

- [XAMPP](https://www.apachefriends.org/) (for Apache + PHP)
- [MariaDB 12.2](https://mariadb.org/download/) (standalone, separate from XAMPP MySQL)
- A modern web browser (Chrome, Firefox, Edge)
- Git

> **Important:** XAMPP's built-in MySQL must be **stopped** in the XAMPP Control Panel.
> Only Apache should be running from XAMPP. MariaDB runs as a separate Windows service.

---

## Installation and Setup

### Step 1 ‚Äî Clone the Repository


git clone https://github.com/[your-repo-url]/COS221-Tripistry.git


Or extract the submitted ZIP archive into your XAMPP web root:


C:\xampp\htdocs\COS221-Tripistry\


### Step 2 ‚Äî Create the Database

Open a terminal and run:


"C:\Program Files\MariaDB 12.2\bin\mysql.exe" -u root -p -e "CREATE DATABASE IF NOT EXISTS tripistry;"


### Step 3 ‚Äî Import the Schema


"C:\Program Files\MariaDB 12.2\bin\mysql.exe" -u root -p tripistry < "sql/create_tables.sql"


### Step 4 ‚Äî Populate the Data


"C:\Program Files\MariaDB 12.2\bin\mysql.exe" -u root -p tripistry < "sql/populate_data.sql"


### Step 5 ‚Äî Configure the Database Connection

Open `Tripistry/config.php` and update the password to match your MariaDB root password:


$mysqli = new mysqli('127.0.0.1', 'root', 'YOUR_PASSWORD', 'tripistry', 3306);

If you have no password set, leave it as an empty string `''`.

### Step 6 ‚Äî Start Apache

Open the XAMPP Control Panel and click **Start** next to **Apache**.
Ensure MariaDB is running as a Windows service (check Services via Win+R ‚Üí `services.msc`).

### Step 7 ‚Äî Open the Application

Navigate to:


http://localhost/COS221-Tripistry/Tripistry/


