## Data Validation

### Client-Side (JavaScript)
- Email format validated using regex before form submission
- Password requirements enforced: minimum 8 characters
- Required fields checked before any API call is made
- Package form validates price > 0, quantity ‚â• 0 and expiry date is set
- Star rating must be selected before review submission

### Server-Side (PHP)
- All inputs sanitised and type-cast before use in SQL queries
- Prepared statements with `bind_param` used throughout ‚Äî no raw SQL string concatenation
- API key validated against database on every protected endpoint
- User role (`user_type`) verified server-side for every agency and traveller endpoint
- Business registration number checked against `businessregistration` table before agency signup
- Duplicate email checked before user registration
- Review submission validates that a confirmed booking exists for the traveller and package

---

## Role-Based Access Control

Access to pages is enforced at the PHP level using `auth.php`:


require_once '../Tripistry/auth.php';
requireRole('travel_agent'); // or 'traveller'


- A traveller visiting an agency page is redirected to the traveller dashboard
- An agency visiting a traveller page is redirected to the agency dashboard
- Any unauthenticated user is redirected to the login page
- This check occurs before any HTML is rendered, preventing partial page exposure

---

## Known Limitations

- Images (`img_url`) for packages, accommodation and attractions are stored as URL references.
  No actual image upload functionality is implemented; placeholder icons are used throughout.
- The application is configured for local development. To deploy to a remote server, update
  all `http://localhost/COS221-Tripistry/` references in JavaScript files to the server URL.
- Password hashing uses SHA-256 (via PHP's `hash()` function) for compatibility with the
  existing dataset. bcrypt (`password_hash`) would be preferred in a production environment.

---

## Git Workflow

The team used a feature-branch workflow:

- `main` ‚Äî stable, submission-ready code only
- `dev` ‚Äî integration branch for merging feature branches
- `feature/[name]` ‚Äî individual feature branches (e.g. `feature/reviews`, `feature/agency-dashboard`)

Commit message format:

[type]: short description

types: feat, fix, refactor, docs, style, chore


Examples:

feat: add GetBookings endpoint with already_reviewed flag
fix: resolve variable scope clash between reviews.js and navbar.js
docs: update README with installation steps
refactor: wrap all traveller JS files in IIFE to prevent global clashes


---

## SQL Files

Located in the `sql/` folder:

| File | Contents |
|------|----------|
| `create_database.sql` | `CREATE DATABASE IF NOT EXISTS tripistry` |
| `create_tables.sql` | All `CREATE TABLE` statements with constraints and indexes |
| `populate_data.sql` | All `INSERT INTO` statements for seed data |

To reimport from scratch:

"C:\Program Files\MariaDB 12.2\bin\mysql.exe" -u root -p -e "DROP DATABASE IF EXISTS tripistry; CREATE DATABASE tripistry;"
"C:\Program Files\MariaDB 12.2\bin\mysql.exe" -u root -p tripistry < sql/create_tables.sql
"C:\Program Files\MariaDB 12.2\bin\mysql.exe" -u root -p tripistry < sql/populate_data.sql



